Slim, stylish and packed with innovative features, the newly launched HONOR X8 smartphone will exceed your expectations — especially when it comes to its awesome photographic and video capabilities. Equally great for budding photographers, casual snappers and professional content creators on the go, the Honor X8 boasts a powerful rear quad camera system that lets you  capture every moment in stunning detail — day, night or in low-light. This quad camera system comprises: Speaking of show-stopping portraits, the HONOR X8 also has a 16MP front camera with a f/2.45 aperture and image resolution of 4,608 x 3,456 pixels, allowing you to snap stellar selfies with enhanced image quality. The 16MP front camera also supports 1080P video shooting with a resolution of 1920x1080 pixels making it brilliant for vloggers. What’s more, the HONOR X8 is equipped with Dual View Recording, which means you can use the front and rear cameras simultaneously to create fun and exciting videos. Whether you’re vlogging your day, recording a special moment with family and friends, or filming a product demo, dual view shows what is captured by both cameras side by side giving you the flexibility and freedom to create engaging content with ease. In fact, the only thing more impressive than the HONOR X8’s photographic and video capabilities is  that these hi-tech features come in a smartphone with an affordable price tag of R4,999. For more information, visit Hihonor.com/za This article was paid for by Honor.